 that Cr substitution of V is an electron trap\nwhile Mo and W are \"repulsive\" centers, mainly due to the minimization of local\nlattice expansion by dopants and electron polarons. The dopants with\n\"repulsive\" interactions to polarons are promising for mobility improvement due\nto larger wavefunction overlap and delocalization of locally concentrated\npolarons.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 7 Aug 2018 18:31:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 17 Sep 2018 16:42:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-09"}
